# Performance Rendering

- Avoid heavy work in render loops and high-frequency event handlers.
- Reuse computed values where possible in hot code paths.
- Keep scene updates incremental; avoid full recompute when a local update is enough.
- Prefer profiling-driven optimization over speculative micro-optimizations.

## How to verify

1. Run the relevant UI flow locally and check for interaction jank.
2. Validate that changed handlers do not allocate unnecessary large objects each frame.
3. Run `yarn build` to ensure no bundling regressions are introduced by changes.
